         <abstract>
            <p>Many existing algorithms for obtaining the eigenvalues and eigenvectors of matrices would make poor use of such a powerful parallel computer as the ILLIAC IV. In this paper, Jacobi's algorithm for real symmetric or complex Hermitian matrices, and a Jacobi-like algorithm for real nonsymmetric matrices developed by P. J. Eberlein, are modified so as to achieve maximum efficiency for the parallel computations.</p>
          </abstract>
